<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>593954</id>
	<title>Some compatible add-ons become "not compatible" from time to time</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Some compatible extensions get magically "not compatible" from time to time.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">When this happens, it's enough to click the "Find updates" button in the Add-ons dialog, and they magically (again) start working.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Later on, they get not compatible again.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">This happens when restarting Firefox or the OS, but now always.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">It doesn't depend on updates to Firefox nor to any other extension.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">This has been a long time issue for me, specially with the Brazilian Portuguese dictionary.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">It happens now with another extension (URL Alias), so I've understood it's an overall Firefox issue.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">I'll attach some screenshots of the issue.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">It always happens with both extensions at the same time; never for one of them only.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">Reproducible: Sometimes</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
